  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9c\u0ddd\u0da8\u0dcf\u0db7\u0dba \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0dbb\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dc0 \u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa leaves the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "BBC Sinhala Service reports that President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa, who fled the Presidential Palace due to public protests on July 9, has left the island early today (July 13).",
        "According to the report to Bibisia that the President has left for Maldives.",
        "Gotabhaya Rajapaksa, who left the country, has reached the Maldives, where a video showing him being taken out of the airport under strict security has been published on social media.",
        "The authorities say that on the night of July 12, after receiving the approval of the immigration officials, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, his wife Ayoma and two others left for the Maldives in a Sri Lankan Air Force plane.",
        "Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena announced on July 9 that he has been informed that the President will resign today (July 13). Accordingly, the people as well as the strugglers are paying close attention to it. It is still uncertain whether President Gotabaya Rajapaksa will actually announce his resignation today.",
        "Before this, it had been reported on several occasions that the President tried to leave the country.",
        "The Hindu newspaper revealed that America has rejected President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa's recent request for an American visa.",
        "The activists emphasized that the President as well as the Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe should step down today.",
        "Although there were earlier reports that the President would not resign without his family members leaving the country safely, neither the speaker nor any other party had made an official statement about it."
      ],
